Zambian Mining Taxes to Reach $500 Million in Two to Three Years

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-06-23T11:31:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/zambian-mining-taxes-to-reach-500-million-in-two-to-three-years.html
Zambian revenue from mining taxes
will rise to $500 million within two to three years, said Kapil
Kapoor, the  World Bank ’s manager for the southern African
nation.  Mining tax receipts will increase from about $300 million
this year, Kapoor said in an e-mailed response to questions from
the capital, Lusaka, today.  Zambia, Africa’s top copper producer, is targeting output
of about 2 million tons a year by 2015,  Situmbeko Musokotwane ,
the finance and national planning minister, said in April.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Mukwita in Lusaka via Johannesburg at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 